<br>
The concept was that as a relief to our &quot;good&quot; guild, a number of us formed an evil guild called the Paw of the Weasel.  Unlike most guilds, you became an officer / leader by killing off the one who currently held the position.  It made it rather interesting.. do you help your guildmate level / get items knowing they will use them one day against you *grins*. Minki managed to become leader at last by dint of clever use of poison...though I believe Ferret ousted her the very next day hehe.<br>
<br>
Some day I would love to recreate the persona of Minki on this server ...Vah Shir rogue of course. <br>
<br>
(A guild based on this concept of course requires very mature players who know each other well and can enjoy the fun without the grief...) <p><img border=0 src="http://home.golden.net/~effinger/sig.jpg" /></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bakanome>Bakanome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 829<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/16/03 7:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4591.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sprit of Fighting.</span><hr size=1> While I would certainly not change the character (I don't roleplay enough anymore to stagnate him), setting up a Church, a proper Church, with priests, knights, missionaries.  That would be just about the most fun I could have roleplaying.  Not a malicious Church of course, but a good Church, dedicated to helping others and spreading the word of Marr.<br>
